xt":"Use an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/NSViewControllerRepresentable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance to create and manage an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/appkit\/nsviewcontroller","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object in your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI interface. Adopt this protocol in one of your app’s custom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instances, and use its methods to create, update, and tear down your view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"controller. The creation and update processes parallel the behavior of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI views, and you use them to configure your view controller with your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app’s current state information. Use the teardown process to remove your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view controller cleanly from your OpenSwiftUI. For example, you might use the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"teardown process to notify other objects that the view controller is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"disappearing.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add your view controller into your OpenSwiftUI interface, create your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSViewControllerRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" instance and add it to your OpenSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interface. The system calls the methods of your custom instance at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate times."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The system doesn’t automatically communicate changes occurring within your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"tex